{{语音变化}}
'''Shm-重复'''是一种[[叠词|叠词]]法。它在一个词的后面加上 '''shm-''' （或者 '''schm-'''）（{{pronounced|ʃm}}。）然后再把增加了“shm”的单词放在原来单词的后面。这种重复通常是用来表示对被修辞的事物的讽刺或贬低，例如Baby-shmaby<ref>{{cite news |author=Holly Raybin |publisher=[[Jews_for_Jesus|Jews for Jesus]] |title=The Baby |url=http://jewsforjesus.org/publications/newsletter/1986_12/baby |date=December 1, 1986 |accessdate=December 12, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120425221159/http://jewsforjesus.org/publications/newsletter/1986_12/baby |archive-date=2012-04-25 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

原来的单词可以是名词，也可以是动词或形容词，例如“Whenever we go to a fancy-schmancy restaurant, we feel like James Bond.”<ref>{{cite book |title=Penn & Teller's how to play with your food |url=https://archive.org/details/penntellershowto00penn |author=Penn Jillette and Teller |authorlink=Penn & Teller |publisher=Villard Books |year=1992 |page=[https://archive.org/details/penntellershowto00penn/page/35 35] |isbn=0-679-74311-1}}</ref>

==构成方法==
参照Andrew Nevins和Bert Vaux2003年的网上调查研究<ref name="bertvaux">{{cite web|url=http://www.academia.edu/209796/Metalinguistic_shmetalinguistic_The_phonology_of_shm-reduplication|title=Metalinguistic, shmetalinguistic: the phonology of shm-reduplication|author=Andrew Nevins, Bert Vaux|year=2003|accessdate=2014-01-03|archive-date=2015-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151216005313/http://www.academia.edu/209796/Metalinguistic_shmetalinguistic_The_phonology_of_shm-reduplication|dead-url=no}}</ref>：
*以一个辅音开始的单词一般去掉开头的辅音，再加上“shm-”例如：table shmable
*以两个辅音开始的单词，有时是把头两个辅音都去掉，有时是只去掉第一个辅音。例如：breakfast shmreakfast，也可作breakfast shmeakfast。
*以元音开始的单词直接加“shm-”，例如：apple shmapple。
*在第一音节非重音的多音节词中，有时在重音音节处加上“shm-”，有时在单词的开头加上“shm-”（见下表）。有时也不重复单词在重音音节前面的成分，例如：incredible shmedible; <ref>Spitzer, Leo. "Confusion Shmooshun". Journal of English and Germanic Philology 51 (1952): 226–33.</ref>
