*一些人用sm-而不用shm-加在含有sh的单词前面。例如：Ashmont Smashmont，而不是 shmashmont。
*以shm开头的单词一般不使用shm重复，但有些人选择改变单词的形式，如shmuck变形为fluck, shpuck, vluck, shmluck等。

== 起源和应用 ==
一般认为，这种用法很可能起源自[[意地绪语|意地绪语]]然后再转移到[[英语|英语]]。也有说法认为shm-重复和土耳其语的m-和[[东斯拉夫语支|东斯拉夫语支]]的sh-有关。<ref name="bertvaux"/><ref>Southern, Mark. ''Contagious Couplings: Transmission of Expressives in Yiddish Echo Phrases.'' Westport: Greenwood, 2005.
</ref>

[[牛津英语字典|牛津英语字典]]中收录最早的英文出处为“I know he made Davy go to the Palace to-day with the idea of hastening on the crisis in his illness... Crisis-shmisis! mocked Barnett disparagingly” (Goller 1929:V.ii.215).。<ref name="bertvaux"/><ref>[http://books.google.com.hk/books?id=KT-cAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA260&lpg=PA260&dq=Goller+1929+I+know+he+made+Davy+go+to+the+Palace+to-day+with+the+idea+of+hastening+on+the+crisis+in+his+illness&source=bl&ots=6tBowD3PfC&sig=c0AkFR3b3aAnCJPkKyay3aKgTEM&hl=zh-CN&sa=X&ei=uX7GUtWuEenZigeXjYHoDA&ved=0CCAQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Goller%201929%20I%20know%20he%20made%20Davy%20go%20to%20the%20Palace%20to-day%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20hastening%20on%20the%20crisis%20in%20his%20illness&f=false] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com.hk/books?id=KT-cAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA260&lpg=PA260&dq=Goller+1929+I+know+he+made+Davy+go+to+the+Palace+to-day+with+the+idea+of+hastening+on+the+crisis+in+his+illness&source=bl&ots=6tBowD3PfC&sig=c0AkFR3b3aAnCJPkKyay3aKgTEM&hl=zh-CN&sa=X&ei=uX7GUtWuEenZigeXjYHoDA&ved=0CCAQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Goller%201929%20I%20know%20he%20made%20Davy%20go%20to%20the%20Palace%20to-day%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20hastening%20on%20the%20crisis%20in%20his%20illness&f=false |date=20140103190924 }}，Oxford Dictionary of Modern Slang，John Ayto，John Simpson</ref>

1960年美国学术期刊《[[美国语言_(杂志)|美国语言]]》的论文《On Yiddish Shm-.》<ref>Feinsilver, Lillian Mermin. "On Yiddish Shm-." ''American Speech'' 36 (1961): 302-3.</ref>提到，shm-重复已经广泛出现在广告、电影和报纸上。

shm-重复也出现在[[现代希伯来语|现代希伯来语]]中，例如[[戴维·本-古里安|戴维·本-古里安]]在1955年3月29日的一次内阁会议中用"{{link-en|Um-Shmum|Um-Shmum}}" （UN Shm-UN）评价联合国。<ref>Moshe Sharett, ''Yoman ishi'' [=Personal Diary], vol. 3, Tel-Aviv: Sifriyat Ma'ariv, 1978, p. 874 (Hebrew).</ref><ref name="Zuckermann">Zuckermann, Ghil'ad (2009), [http://www.zuckermann.org/pdf/Hybridity_versus_Revivability.pdf Hybridity versus Revivability: Multiple Causation, Forms and Patterns] {{Wayback|url=http://www.zuckermann.org/pdf/Hybridity_versus_Revivability.pdf |date=20180722010237 }}. In ''Journal of Language Contact'', Varia 2: 40–67, p. 49, 作者也参考了Haig (2001) 以及 Lewis (1967).</ref>

其他语言也有类似的“加辅音+重复”现象，如[[卡纳达语|卡纳达语]]中的gi-重复<ref>{{Citation |page= |work=University of Pennsylvania Working Papers in Linguistics |publication-date=1999 |volume=6.3 |issue= |title=Echo Reduplication in Kannada: Implications for a Theory of Word-formation |author=Jeffrey Lidz |url=http://www.ai.mit.edu/projects/dm/lidz-echo.pdf |accessdate=January 3, 2014 |archive-date=2014-09-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140910044755/http://www.ai.mit.edu/projects/dm/lidz-echo.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>表示与某事物相关的事物。

